f=Engineering/aegis/custom/secure-code-review/SKILL.md · in=secure-code-review aegis's deep, human-paced security read specific change pass dev's code-review-standards routes diff touches new external surface, auth path, secret handling, threat-modeled hot spot. dev's review asks "is correct safe enough merge" across diff, asks "can specific change attacked" diffs warrant specialist. verdict quinn's S-tier input. **This skill aegis's primary teeth interpreted stacks (Python/JS/TS) agent code** fully stack-agnostic, vuln-pipeline's harness detector native-code-only. deployment (LLM agents Python/JS/TS), real findings come adversarial read plus vuln-pipeline's web/LLM detection classes, ASAN crashes. · p=breaches enter through code passed normal review looked correct because reviewer wasn't reading attacker. dedicated security review reads adversarially: "does happy path work" "what malicious path do." It's depth complement vuln-pipeline's breadth, focused threat model dev's routing say risk concentrates. · wu=Triggers: dev's code-review-standards routing risky surface (the primary entry), "security review this," "is change safe," auth/crypto/input-handling diffs, anything touching high-likelihood threat-model surface, pre-release security-adjacent changes (quinn's matrix row). · st:/ Protocol=`Risky diff arrives (dev routing / threat-model surface / self-flagged) \· -> Load context: the diff + stack-profile sinks/sources + THREAT_MODEL.md rows it touches \· -> Read adversarially by category (STRIDE lens; OWASP/CWE specifics): \· WEB: input validation \· authn \· authZ (per-object, not just per-route) \· secrets/keys \· \· injection (SQL/command/template/LDAP) \· SSRF/XXE \· deserialization \· crypto misuse \·` · in=**Read attacker, author.** changed sink, ask what hostile input reaches what input achieves whether intended input works. author already checked happy path; your job paths. **Authorization per-object, per-route.** common real-world hole: authentication present, authorization checked route specific resource (IDOR). Verify change checks actor act *this* object, new path. **Trace untrusted data sink.** Follow tainted input entry SQL, shell, template, filesystem, outbound request, deserializer. parameterized query string-concatenated one still injection completeness matters. **Secrets, crypto, errors.** secrets code/logs/errors; crypto uses vetted primitives correctly (no homemade, ECB, static IV/nonce); error messages don't leak stack traces, queries, internal structure untrusted callers. **New dependency new surface.** diff adding dependency imports vulnerabilities transitive tree; flag vuln-pipeline/ops CVE tracking question whether it's warranted (dev's boring-is-a-feature, security edition). **Findings exploit-sketched.** finding names it's reached what yields, `file:line`, fix actionable discipline dev's reviews, plus attack path. Vague "this looks insecure" finding. **Threats outlive diffs.** review reveals threat class (not instance), update threat model imported skill fixed line code shouldn't erase lesson (the harness's threats-vs-vulns litmus). · of=`## Security Review: [change] — routed by [dev ref / threat surface] \· Threat context: [THREAT_MODEL.md rows touched] \· Categories reviewed: [input \· authn \· authz \· injection \· secrets \· crypto \· SSRF \· deser \· deps] \· Findings: [F-id \· class \· file:line \· exploit sketch \· severity \· fix] → vuln-pipeline schema \· ` · pr=**Read adversarially** malicious path, happy one., **AuthZ per-object** IDOR hole one normal review misses most., **Trace taint sink, completely** one missed concatenation injection., **Every finding carries exploit sketch fix file:line** actionable it's finding., **New dependencies new attack surface** warranted, flagged., **Threats outlive diff** instance fixed, class recorded threat model. · f=threat model area review universal security grounds (OWASP/CWE), flag surface needs threat model (seed what review found)., Diff large review adversarially depth request split (dev's over-broad-diff integrity concern, security edition) rather skim stamp SECURE., Uncertain exploitability route vuln-pipeline execution-verification sandbox rather guess; couldn't prove safe" finding, pass. · b:with Other Skills=**dev/code-review-standards** per-PR gate ROUTES risky surfaces here; specialist depth, replacement dev's review., **vuln-pipeline** (sibling) breadth-across-a-surface; depth-on-a-diff. Uncertain findings route pipeline sandboxed verification., **verified-patching** (sibling) fixes what finds; findings use shared vuln-pipeline schema., **quinn/test-strategy**: verdict S-tier release-gate matrix requires security-adjacent changes., **marketplace/threat-model**: consumed context, updated new threat class surfaces. · h2:Stack Notes (dated)=`assets/stack-notes-laravel-security-2026-07.md` Laravel security review checklist layer. Applies stack-profile names Laravel/PHP; adopted marketplace (ECC) 2026-07-10; method conflicts resolve skill.